WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.386
[marker scribbling]

2
00:00:12.929 --> 00:00:14.514
[marker scribbling]

3
00:00:17.058 --> 00:00:19.144
[melancholy music playing]

4
00:00:19.728 --> 00:00:21.229
Isla. what are you telling me?

5
00:00:24.190 --> 00:00:25.859
Lev. I can't marry you.

6
00:00:29.404 --> 00:00:30.447
[Lev] This is a joke.

7
00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:32.574
-[Isla] Lev.
-[Lev] I can't believe this is happening.

8
00:00:32.657 --> 00:00:35.952
-Lev. Honey. just listen.
-Please… please don't honey me.

9
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:38.621
Okay. you were the one who begged
to get back together with me.

10
00:00:38.705 --> 00:00:42.375
What kinda asshole breaks up with someone
the night before the wedding?

11
00:00:42.459 --> 00:00:45.545
Well. at least I didn't do it
at the altar.

12
00:00:45.628 --> 00:00:48.214
Oh. thank you. Do you know
what it took to get my bubbe here?

13
00:00:48.298 --> 00:00:51.176
We had to crush a Xanax. put it in
her apple juice to get her on the plane.

14
00:00:51.259 --> 00:00:55.472
-That's how much I wanted her to meet you.
-I never asked you to drug your grandma.

15
00:00:55.555 --> 00:00:56.431
Isla. stop.

16
00:00:56.514 --> 00:00:59.726
Please. just… stop.

17
00:01:02.228 --> 00:01:03.354
You are so selfish.

18
00:01:05.523 --> 00:01:09.277
I… I can't believe I'm saying this.
but ho… honestly…

19
00:01:11.613 --> 00:01:13.031
I think you're a bad person.

20
00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:17.035
[sad music playing]

21
00:01:17.118 --> 00:01:18.119
Goodbye. Isla.

22
00:01:21.498 --> 00:01:22.332
[scoffs]

23
00:01:24.918 --> 00:01:29.464
[Isla] Ladies and gentlemen.
that is how you lose a guy in ten minutes.

24
00:01:29.547 --> 00:01:30.423
[sighs]

25
00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:34.135
[Isla] Since then.
I've been living in Ness' guest house

26
00:01:34.219 --> 00:01:35.929
to give Lev time to move out.

27
00:01:36.012 --> 00:01:38.598
It's been a chance to mourn. reflect.

28
00:01:38.681 --> 00:01:41.518
and be woken up every morning
by Ness doing CrossFit.

29
00:01:41.601 --> 00:01:44.145
-[Ness grunts]
-[Isla gasps]

30
00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:45.271
God. Ness!

31
00:01:45.355 --> 00:01:49.025
Sorry. I have to vocalize.
otherwise I can't activate my glutes.

32
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:50.401
I only have 200 more.

33
00:01:50.485 --> 00:01:51.486
[Ness exhales]

34
00:01:51.569 --> 00:01:54.322
[Isla] Also. I can't stop thinking
about what Lev said.

35
00:01:54.405 --> 00:01:56.032
Am I a bad person?

36
00:01:56.116 --> 00:01:59.452
When I really examine my daily choices.
I feel like he might be right.

37
00:01:59.536 --> 00:02:01.246
[upbeat rhythmic music playing]

38
00:02:01.329 --> 00:02:02.705
[brakes squeal]

39
00:02:04.207 --> 00:02:05.208
[door lock chirps]

40
00:02:06.584 --> 00:02:08.419
Goddammit! Isla!

41
00:02:08.503 --> 00:02:12.173
♪ I'm gonna tell you today
I'm gonna tell you tomorrow ♪

42
00:02:12.257 --> 00:02:13.424
[clanking]

43
00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:16.678
♪ All I need is you loving me… ♪

44
00:02:16.761 --> 00:02:18.388
-So what. did you get a...
-[chair clanks]

45
00:02:18.471 --> 00:02:20.098
[shrieks] Goddammit!

46
00:02:20.181 --> 00:02:23.017
♪ As long as I can breathe ♪

47
00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:29.816
Oh. goddammit.

48
00:02:30.525 --> 00:02:31.568
[Isla] Lev was right.

49
00:02:31.651 --> 00:02:33.069
I'm a dick.

50
00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:34.112
[grunts] Oh!

51
00:02:34.195 --> 00:02:35.363
-[glass shatters]
-[screams]

52
00:02:35.446 --> 00:02:36.322
Oh!

53
00:02:36.406 --> 00:02:37.323
God!

54
00:02:37.407 --> 00:02:39.200
[panting] My hands get wet.

55
00:02:39.284 --> 00:02:41.244
[hip-hop music playing]

56
00:02:49.586 --> 00:02:51.212
Thanks for driving me from the remote lot.

57
00:02:51.296 --> 00:02:54.424
I still can't believe they make us park
all the way under the highway.

58
00:02:54.507 --> 00:02:57.177
At least this way
we get to spend more time together.

59
00:02:57.260 --> 00:02:59.679
Do you know
the dancers don't have health insurance?

60
00:02:59.762 --> 00:03:01.681
I mean. I'm… I'm not defending them.

61
00:03:01.764 --> 00:03:05.268
but they are always talking about
how broke the team is.

62
00:03:05.351 --> 00:03:07.187
Jackie. you just parked

63
00:03:07.270 --> 00:03:11.107
between your brother's Maserati
and your other brother's Maserati.

64
00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:13.318
[hip-hop music continues]

65
00:03:13.985 --> 00:03:15.028
I gotta go.

66
00:03:16.237 --> 00:03:20.116
I think I speak
on behalf of the entire Waves organization

67
00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:22.619
when I tell you
we couldn't be more excited right now.

68
00:03:22.702 --> 00:03:25.288
as we welcome Tommy White to Los Angeles.

69
00:03:25.371 --> 00:03:27.165
-[applause]
-Let's jump into it. Any questions?

70
00:03:27.248 --> 00:03:30.251
Tommy White.
you're the heartthrob of the league.

71
00:03:30.335 --> 00:03:32.337
Is there any truth
to you dating Kaia Gerber?

72
00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:35.131
Okay. we're not gonna talk about
Tommy's love life.

73
00:03:35.215 --> 00:03:38.801
Although. with a face like that. I'm sure
there's always more than one girl.

74
00:03:38.885 --> 00:03:41.054
-[all laughing]
-Yeah. Kaia and I are just friends.

75
00:03:41.638 --> 00:03:43.348
We met in the greenroom at Hot Ones.

76
00:03:43.431 --> 00:03:45.975
Tommy. what's been your favorite part
of Los Angeles so far?

77
00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:48.728
Oh. without a doubt. the Jurassic Park
ride at Universal Studios.

78
00:03:48.811 --> 00:03:52.690
I freaked out and… and punched
the spitty one. the one that got Newman.

79
00:03:52.774 --> 00:03:57.779
Uh. Tommy also has said he's excited
about joining the fire recovery efforts.

80
00:03:57.862 --> 00:03:58.863
There was a fire?

81
00:03:58.947 --> 00:03:59.822
Let's stop it.

82
00:03:59.906 --> 00:04:01.616
He's really happy to be here.

83
00:04:01.699 --> 00:04:03.785
Tommy already loves LA.

84
00:04:03.868 --> 00:04:05.912
["I Love L.A." by Randy Newman plays]

85
00:04:05.995 --> 00:04:07.288
We love it!

86
00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:11.542
♪ I love LA ♪

87
00:04:11.626 --> 00:04:13.211
[cameras clicking]

88
00:04:13.294 --> 00:04:14.545
♪ We love it ♪

89
00:04:17.048 --> 00:04:18.341
♪ We love it ♪

90
00:04:19.676 --> 00:04:21.636
Did Tommy just smile at you?

91
00:04:22.303 --> 00:04:23.137
I don't know.

92
00:04:23.221 --> 00:04:25.181
I just got an email
that my kid's got lice.

93
00:04:25.265 --> 00:04:27.100
What neighborhood
did you settle in. Tommy?

94
00:04:27.183 --> 00:04:28.518
Actually. I have no home.

95
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:30.645
-I'm homeless.
-[Isla] No. no. no.

96
00:04:30.728 --> 00:04:32.897
He's actually staying
at a very exclusive hotel.

97
00:04:32.981 --> 00:04:33.815
[Tommy] It's nice.

98
00:04:33.898 --> 00:04:36.985
It's hard to feel like a part
of the community until I have a house.

99
00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:39.696
I need those things
that trees have in the dirt.

100
00:04:39.779 --> 00:04:41.281
the branches that are underground.

101
00:04:41.364 --> 00:04:42.573
-Roots.
-Yeah. roots.

102
00:04:42.657 --> 00:04:44.701
And that's impossible in a hotel.

103
00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:46.869
That's really sad and beautiful.

104
00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:50.456
Isla. at what point
does temporary housing become negligence?

105
00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:52.333
We will find Tommy a home.

106
00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:55.962
We're very invested in Tommy. which is why
we're paying him $200 million.

107
00:04:56.045 --> 00:04:56.879
Next question.

108
00:04:57.463 --> 00:05:00.383
[male reporter] Tommy. do you think
you and Travis can share the ball?

109
00:05:03.177 --> 00:05:04.595
What the hell. you guys?

110
00:05:04.679 --> 00:05:07.974
How hard is it
to find a McMansion in Los Angeles?

111
00:05:08.057 --> 00:05:09.142
It's brutal out there.

112
00:05:09.225 --> 00:05:12.145
Look. every house we've looked at
has been rented to a Bachelor spinoff

113
00:05:12.228 --> 00:05:14.480
or some oligarch's kid
transferring to USC.

114
00:05:14.564 --> 00:05:17.483
Okay. Sandy. what about your mom?
Isn't she a real estate agent?

115
00:05:17.567 --> 00:05:19.319
She just said that
to get on Selling Sunset.

116
00:05:19.402 --> 00:05:21.821
then they said she was too old.
so now she does nothing again.

117
00:05:21.904 --> 00:05:23.197
[Ali] We are on it. I promise.

118
00:05:23.281 --> 00:05:26.534
By sundown. Tommy White will be
in his own personal Versailles.

119
00:05:26.617 --> 00:05:28.119
We got a big problem.

120
00:05:28.202 --> 00:05:29.120
Like. real big.

121
00:05:29.203 --> 00:05:31.956
Jackie. she's your girlfriend. Explain.

122
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:33.333
She made a TikTok.

123
00:05:33.416 --> 00:05:35.376
[Ness] No. not just a TikTok.

124
00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:37.920
A TikTok with 1.5 million views.

125
00:05:38.004 --> 00:05:39.422
-What?
-Screen-share.

126
00:05:39.505 --> 00:05:42.133
POV. you're a professional dancer
for the Waves.

127
00:05:42.216 --> 00:05:44.552
It's 5:30 a.m.. and you just got to work.

128
00:05:44.635 --> 00:05:47.138
and your parking lot's giving
major crime scene energy.

129
00:05:47.221 --> 00:05:49.182
Security? Oh no. babe.
it's a trust-based system.

130
00:05:49.265 --> 00:05:51.351
And here's where the magic happens.

131
00:05:51.434 --> 00:05:54.103
No mirrors. no heat.
one broken Bluetooth speaker.

132
00:05:54.187 --> 00:05:57.315
I wonder if Tommy White's
$200 million locker room looks like this.

133
00:05:57.398 --> 00:05:59.025
Don't worry. We get paid in exposure.

134
00:05:59.108 --> 00:06:01.402
Anyway. we slay.
even if the workplace doesn't.

135
00:06:01.486 --> 00:06:03.946
Hashtag dancer life. Hashtag go LA Waves.

136
00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:05.490
Hashtag minimum wage.

137
00:06:05.573 --> 00:06:07.033
[Ali] That little B!

138
00:06:07.617 --> 00:06:09.077
-Also. she is so cute.
-I know.

139
00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:11.454
Oh my God. Ness. are you. like. emotional?

140
00:06:11.537 --> 00:06:13.498
No. I was just really in
her point of view.

141
00:06:13.581 --> 00:06:16.167
-Oh God. there are thousands of comments.
-[Isla. Ali] What?

142
00:06:16.250 --> 00:06:18.628
No. no. no. John Legend said.
"Wow. that part."

143
00:06:18.711 --> 00:06:21.130
"Isla Gordon ought to be
ashamed of herself."

144
00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:25.051
Oh my God. a Cynthia Erivo fan account
said I'm the Wicked Bitch of the West.

145
00:06:25.134 --> 00:06:26.094
So clever.

146
00:06:26.177 --> 00:06:28.805
And Jackie commented. "That's my boo!"

147
00:06:28.888 --> 00:06:30.932
I had to.
so people knew she had a boyfriend.

148
00:06:31.015 --> 00:06:34.102
but just because I hearted it
doesn't mean I liked it in my heart.

149
00:06:34.185 --> 00:06:36.729
Well. tell your little girlfriend
to take it down.

150
00:06:36.813 --> 00:06:37.647
Yeah.

151
00:06:37.730 --> 00:06:40.108
Also. find out
what kind of selfie stick she used

152
00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:42.610
because Bituin and I need
a little more stabilization.

153
00:06:43.361 --> 00:06:45.530
-I don't know that she'll listen to me.
-Make her!

154
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:48.741
We don't need some beautiful. ethnic
Disney princess telling us we're cheap.

155
00:06:48.825 --> 00:06:52.078
Know what? I'll call Bernie and ask him if
we can fire her for a breach of contract.

156
00:06:52.161 --> 00:06:54.622
Yeah. Dad fired the entire dance team
every five years.

157
00:06:54.705 --> 00:06:56.499
Loved himself a fresh batch of fillies.

158
00:06:56.582 --> 00:06:59.877
He'd call up Hugh Hefner and say.
"Hef. send me your best dancers."

159
00:06:59.961 --> 00:07:01.504
-"I want curves. I want--"
-No.

160
00:07:02.088 --> 00:07:07.301
We are not firing any of the dancers.
and we are not silencing Sofia.

161
00:07:07.385 --> 00:07:09.762
We are better than that.
I am better than that.

162
00:07:10.304 --> 00:07:11.889
-You are?
-Yes.

163
00:07:11.973 --> 00:07:13.683
At least I am now.

164
00:07:13.766 --> 00:07:16.144
Jackie. I want you to tell Sofia

165
00:07:16.227 --> 00:07:19.439
that I had no idea the dancers
were working under such conditions.

166
00:07:19.522 --> 00:07:20.982
and I promise to fix them.

167
00:07:21.065 --> 00:07:24.068
and please tell Sofia
I'd like to sit down with her.

168
00:07:24.152 --> 00:07:26.154
[gentle music playing]

169
00:07:32.994 --> 00:07:36.497
So. Tommy. this is George Clooney's house.

170
00:07:36.581 --> 00:07:39.167
He's on Broadway
doing an adaptation of Syriana.

171
00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:41.752
Damn. He looks a lot different
than I remember.

172
00:07:41.836 --> 00:07:44.088
No. no. no. that's his best friend.
Richard Kind.

173
00:07:44.172 --> 00:07:47.550
Yeah. George is a big LA Waves fan
and is willing to rent this out to you.

174
00:07:47.633 --> 00:07:49.927
That's so cool.
Have you guys seen Ocean's Eleven?

175
00:07:50.011 --> 00:07:51.554
-[smacks lips] Yes.
-Of course. yes.

176
00:07:51.637 --> 00:07:55.808
I just saw it and did not get it at all.
I gotta go back and watch the first ten.

177
00:07:56.517 --> 00:07:59.187
Hey. an upstairs.
That's probably where the bedrooms are.

178
00:08:00.897 --> 00:08:03.149
And this is the primary.

179
00:08:03.232 --> 00:08:05.943
The mattress cost more than
my first car. [laughs]

180
00:08:07.069 --> 00:08:09.572
Yeah. I… I don't know
about this thread count.

181
00:08:10.198 --> 00:08:12.158
Would you sleep on this bed. Sandy?

182
00:08:12.658 --> 00:08:15.578
Uh. probably not. I travel
with my own pillowcase and sheets.

183
00:08:15.661 --> 00:08:17.246
I get rashes from most detergents.

184
00:08:17.830 --> 00:08:19.081
You're a little freak. huh?

185
00:08:19.165 --> 00:08:19.999
[chuckles]

186
00:08:20.958 --> 00:08:23.252
I'm gonna go check out the bowling alley.

187
00:08:25.129 --> 00:08:26.130
[Ali gulps]

188
00:08:26.756 --> 00:08:28.299
Dude. he was totally hitting on you.

189
00:08:28.382 --> 00:08:29.884
-Tommy? No way.
-Yeah.

190
00:08:30.843 --> 00:08:34.180
I guess it was flirty for him to call me
a little freak while perched on a bed.

191
00:08:34.263 --> 00:08:35.848
but he's straight. right?

192
00:08:35.932 --> 00:08:36.933
That's what I thought.

193
00:08:37.016 --> 00:08:40.520
but maybe he's into pasty. anxious men
with good posture. Get on that.

194
00:08:40.603 --> 00:08:43.731
I can't hook up with a player.
That's… that's not professional.

195
00:08:43.814 --> 00:08:46.567
It's nothing a delicately-worded letter
to HR can't take care of.

196
00:08:47.568 --> 00:08:50.613
I should go check on Tommy.
I'm worried he'll break George's Oscar.

197
00:08:51.239 --> 00:08:53.241
[upbeat music playing]

198
00:08:58.454 --> 00:09:00.623
[scoffs] Lev blocked me?

199
00:09:01.207 --> 00:09:02.750
-[knock on door]
-You wanted to see me?

200
00:09:02.833 --> 00:09:04.752
Hi. Sofia. yes. come on in.

201
00:09:04.835 --> 00:09:06.754
I just wanted to catch up.

202
00:09:06.837 --> 00:09:11.884
[inhales] Have you seen…
the new murder show?

203
00:09:11.968 --> 00:09:13.844
I know you want me to take down the video.
but I won't.

204
00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:17.098
I would never. okay? Freedom of speech.

205
00:09:17.181 --> 00:09:18.474
Second Amendment.

206
00:09:18.558 --> 00:09:20.393
-[Sofia] Mm. first Amendment.
-Even better.

207
00:09:20.476 --> 00:09:22.061
-Mm.
-You know. I just wanted to say

208
00:09:22.144 --> 00:09:25.356
that I was already planning on
surprising you girls with a tasty perk.

209
00:09:25.439 --> 00:09:30.570
It might not be a lot of cash.
but there is a lot of dough.

210
00:09:30.653 --> 00:09:32.655
Oh God. don't say
you're offering us a pizza party.

211
00:09:32.738 --> 00:09:34.782
No. of course not.

212
00:09:34.865 --> 00:09:35.908
I would never do that.

213
00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:39.412
Look. I've written up a list of demands.
and it's what we think we fairly deserve.

214
00:09:39.495 --> 00:09:41.163
I will read this right away.

215
00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:45.251
I want you to know that
the Waves dancers are a priority for me.

216
00:09:45.751 --> 00:09:47.378
I think you guys deserve the world.

217
00:09:47.461 --> 00:09:49.046
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

218
00:09:50.006 --> 00:09:50.881
Thank you.

219
00:09:51.382 --> 00:09:52.383
[chuckles]

220
00:09:54.594 --> 00:09:56.262
Isla. can I just say that. um.

221
00:09:57.013 --> 00:09:59.056
it really means a lot
that you're doing this.

222
00:09:59.640 --> 00:10:00.558
Thank you.

223
00:10:03.728 --> 00:10:06.063
These demands are insane.
We can't afford this.

224
00:10:06.147 --> 00:10:08.566
We can't afford or don't want to afford.

225
00:10:08.649 --> 00:10:11.193
They want better benefits than we have.
and ours aren't that great.

226
00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.695
They want maternity leave?

227
00:10:12.778 --> 00:10:13.821
I mean. that's great.

228
00:10:13.904 --> 00:10:16.741
It's beautiful. empowering.
but pregnant dancers? [scoffs]

229
00:10:16.824 --> 00:10:19.201
Nobody wants to see
a baby bump under a crop top.

230
00:10:19.285 --> 00:10:20.703
-Oh!
-[Isla] They work so hard.

231
00:10:20.786 --> 00:10:24.290
Dancing while people are on their phones
and going to the bathroom.

232
00:10:24.373 --> 00:10:25.541
We have to pay them more.

233
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:29.211
Dad always said their payment was a chance
to dance in front of lonely. rich men

234
00:10:29.295 --> 00:10:32.506
who can make 'em their wives or at least
keep 'em as a little side piece.

235
00:10:32.590 --> 00:10:34.342
We can't take on any more expenses.

236
00:10:34.425 --> 00:10:36.469
Marcus's statue alone
is costing us a fortune.

237
00:10:36.552 --> 00:10:37.720
We're on the fifth revision

238
00:10:37.803 --> 00:10:40.014
because he didn't like
the way they sculpted his calves.

239
00:10:40.097 --> 00:10:42.683
Isla. you know all this.
Is this about Lev?

