Okay. [exhales]

481
00:20:47.579 --> 00:20:49.164
-I'll do what I can.
-[Diane exhales]

482
00:20:49.248 --> 00:20:51.458
Like. in a real way.

483
00:20:51.541 --> 00:20:52.417
[sighs]

484
00:20:52.501 --> 00:20:54.628
-That's all I needed to hear.
-Yeah.

485
00:20:54.711 --> 00:20:56.630
[Isla] Do I smell like apple juice?

486
00:20:56.713 --> 00:20:58.840
[happy music playing]

487
00:21:01.260 --> 00:21:06.139
Welcome to the brand-new
Waves City Dancers dressing room.

488
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:07.933
sponsored by Sephora.

489
00:21:08.016 --> 00:21:10.352
Also. you're all getting four tickets
for friends and family.

490
00:21:10.435 --> 00:21:12.145
[excited chatter]

491
00:21:12.729 --> 00:21:15.148
You should be very proud.
You helped make this happen.

492
00:21:15.732 --> 00:21:17.693
Yeah. Diane's actually kinda inspired me.

493
00:21:18.777 --> 00:21:20.529
She actually offered me an internship.

494
00:21:20.612 --> 00:21:22.781
What? Well. that's… that's amazing!

495
00:21:23.573 --> 00:21:26.702
Thing is. though. it's…
it's in Washington.

496
00:21:27.577 --> 00:21:31.206
As in Mount Washington.
like the neighborhood in Los Angeles?

497
00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:32.791
As in Washington. D.C.

498
00:21:34.584 --> 00:21:35.419
[Isla] All right.

499
00:21:35.502 --> 00:21:37.587
Well. I just wanna say

500
00:21:37.671 --> 00:21:41.800
that the LA Waves wouldn't be the same
without the Waves City Dancers.

501
00:21:41.883 --> 00:21:45.012
so we are going to give you
a raise and health insurance.

502
00:21:45.595 --> 00:21:48.140
That said.
do not pull a stunt like that again.

503
00:21:48.223 --> 00:21:49.224
Seriously.

504
00:21:49.308 --> 00:21:51.685
And. Jackie. would you mind passing out
the new contracts?

505
00:21:53.228 --> 00:21:55.022
Wow. Isla Gordon.

506
00:21:55.647 --> 00:21:58.483
Tougher to crack than I expected.
but eventually you caved.

507
00:21:59.276 --> 00:22:01.111
I mean. did the right thing.

508
00:22:01.194 --> 00:22:03.405
Mm. And maybe now you'll go on the record

509
00:22:03.488 --> 00:22:05.991
and say that you were wrong.
and I am a good person?

510
00:22:06.074 --> 00:22:08.577
Girl. you have got to get over that.

511
00:22:09.244 --> 00:22:12.289
Diane. it's been… interesting.

512
00:22:12.372 --> 00:22:14.708
and I really admire you as a person.

513
00:22:15.292 --> 00:22:17.127
and I hope we never interact again.

514
00:22:17.210 --> 00:22:19.212
[chuckles] Uh. not so fast.

515
00:22:19.713 --> 00:22:21.840
The girls have one more request.

516
00:22:22.507 --> 00:22:24.968
Fine. As long as it doesn't cost me
any more money.

517
00:22:29.890 --> 00:22:30.766
Lev.

518
00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:34.144
Lev.

519
00:22:35.479 --> 00:22:36.646
Isla. what are you doing here?

520
00:22:36.730 --> 00:22:40.275
I thought we agreed that I had until five
so we wouldn't see each other.

521
00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:43.320
I want to talk to you.
Wait. are you taking the sconces?

522
00:22:43.403 --> 00:22:45.364
Yes. I bought them.

523
00:22:45.864 --> 00:22:50.452
Also. I'm taking the golf clubs
that I bought you that you never use.

524
00:22:50.535 --> 00:22:52.537
You and my cousin are the same height.

525
00:22:52.621 --> 00:22:54.581
-Wait. Lev.
-[Lev exhales]

526
00:22:57.125 --> 00:23:00.796
I hated the way things ended between us.
and I want you to know that

527
00:23:01.797 --> 00:23:03.173
I never wanted to hurt you.

528
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:07.010
And I'm so sorry.

529
00:23:07.969 --> 00:23:09.054
I appreciate that.

530
00:23:09.137 --> 00:23:10.097
[softly] Yeah.

531
00:23:10.180 --> 00:23:13.725
And even though you blocked me
on all social media.

532
00:23:13.809 --> 00:23:14.643
Uh-huh.

533
00:23:14.726 --> 00:23:19.898
I care about you
and really hope we can be friends someday.

534
00:23:19.981 --> 00:23:21.108
[Lev sighs]

535
00:23:23.610 --> 00:23:26.071
You know I don't regret
everything that I said.

536
00:23:26.571 --> 00:23:28.240
[melancholy music playing]

537
00:23:29.324 --> 00:23:30.992
But you're not a bad person.

538
00:23:33.370 --> 00:23:35.497
And you were probably right
to call off the wedding.

539
00:23:35.580 --> 00:23:38.417
And you were right that
it would've been way worse at the altar.

540
00:23:38.500 --> 00:23:39.334
[softly] Yeah.

541
00:23:40.043 --> 00:23:42.379
[both chuckle]

542
00:23:48.552 --> 00:23:49.719
Okay.

543
00:23:50.637 --> 00:23:52.389
We shouldn't get back together.
shouldn't we?

544
00:23:52.472 --> 00:23:54.224
Oh my God. No.

545
00:23:55.434 --> 00:23:58.103
And please don't joke like that.
It's too soon.

546
00:23:58.603 --> 00:24:00.564
I'm still really mad.

547
00:24:04.484 --> 00:24:07.320
Okay. I'm just gonna walk around
the neighborhood until you're done.

548
00:24:10.031 --> 00:24:11.366
[exhales]

549
00:24:17.456 --> 00:24:18.832
[phone vibrates]

550
00:24:29.551 --> 00:24:32.762
[Ness] I gotta go to the bathroom.
What the hell is this halftime surprise?

551
00:24:32.846 --> 00:24:36.433
[announcer] Make some noise
for your Waves City Dancers.

552
00:24:36.516 --> 00:24:38.643
["Get Up" by Ciara
feat. Chamillionaire playing]

553
00:24:39.811 --> 00:24:42.314
♪ Get up. get up. get up ♪

554
00:24:42.397 --> 00:24:44.983
♪ He said. "Hi. my name is so-and-so" ♪

555
00:24:45.066 --> 00:24:47.319
♪ "Baby. can you tell me yours" ♪

556
00:24:47.402 --> 00:24:48.236
Oh!

557
00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:50.739
♪ "You look like you came to do one thing"
Set it off ♪

558
00:24:50.822 --> 00:24:52.073
♪ I started on the left ♪

559
00:24:52.157 --> 00:24:54.618
♪ Then I had to take him to the right ♪

560
00:24:54.701 --> 00:24:58.038
♪ He was out of breath
But he kept on dancin' all night ♪

561
00:24:58.121 --> 00:25:00.457
-♪ Get up ♪
-♪ Ooh. ah ♪

562
00:25:00.540 --> 00:25:03.126
♪ The way you look at me
I'm feelin' you. uh ♪

563
00:25:03.210 --> 00:25:04.503
♪ Ah. I feel it ♪

564
00:25:04.586 --> 00:25:07.047
♪ I just can't help it
Tryin' to keep it cool. uh ♪

565
00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:10.091
♪ The club is jumpin' now
So get up ♪

566
00:25:10.175 --> 00:25:11.801
♪ Now beat 'em down to the floor ♪

567
00:25:11.885 --> 00:25:13.845
♪ Beat 'em down to the floor ♪

568
00:25:13.929 --> 00:25:15.472
♪ Choo-choo-choo-choo ♪

569
00:25:15.555 --> 00:25:17.557
♪ Choo-choo-choo-choo ♪

570
00:25:17.641 --> 00:25:19.309
♪ It's rocket time. it's rocket time ♪

571
00:25:19.392 --> 00:25:21.603
♪ Get pretty girl. rock
So take a picture ♪

572
00:25:21.686 --> 00:25:23.063
♪ Ching-ching-ching-ching ♪

573
00:25:23.146 --> 00:25:25.065
♪ Ching-ching-ching-ching ♪

574
00:25:26.024 --> 00:25:27.317
Yeah!

575
00:25:27.400 --> 00:25:29.277
-[crowd cheering]
-All right!

576
00:25:30.195 --> 00:25:31.154
Yeah!

577
00:25:31.238 --> 00:25:32.489
That was so fun.

578
00:25:32.572 --> 00:25:34.783
[gentle music playing]

579
00:25:35.951 --> 00:25:38.119
What can you take with Accutane?

580
00:25:38.203 --> 00:25:39.871
-[beeping]
-Hey. what's up. man?

581
00:25:40.580 --> 00:25:41.665
You. uh… you free tonight?

582
00:25:42.791 --> 00:25:47.504
Uh… I was going to watch
a couple of eps of Formula One.

583
00:25:47.587 --> 00:25:48.505
Uh. why?

584
00:25:49.631 --> 00:25:52.300
Nah. I was just...
I was thinking. you know...

585
00:25:54.427 --> 00:25:55.637
maybe we do this.

586
00:25:56.137 --> 00:25:57.931
["Teeth" by Mallrat playing]

587
00:26:06.565 --> 00:26:07.899
Also. I need a place to stay.

588
00:26:07.983 --> 00:26:10.360
It seemed like
you're someone who keeps extra towels.

589
00:26:11.027 --> 00:26:13.655
That's. um… not wrong.

590
00:26:13.738 --> 00:26:14.864
Let's go.

591
00:26:18.493 --> 00:26:19.661
[car door opens]

592
00:26:20.495 --> 00:26:22.205
["Teeth" continues playing]

593
00:26:27.419 --> 00:26:29.421
["Teeth" continues playing]

594
00:27:30.440 --> 00:27:32.400
[music ends]
